    {
      "uuid": "9768c2a0-829f-4ef2-acad-ba09cb2d1c57",
      "text": " The 2008 Chevrolet Express 2500 shown in the listing has an 8-cylinder engine, so you can expect:\n\n- City: 12-14 MPG\n- Highway: 15-17 MPG\n- Combined: 13-15 MPG\n\nThese numbers assume:\n- No heavy cargo\n- Regular maintenance\n- Normal driving conditions\n\nReal-world fuel economy could be lower if:\n- Carrying heavy loads\n- Lots of city/stop-and-go driving\n- Aggressive driving\n- Poor maintenance\n- Using the A/C heavily\n- Towing (it has 10,000lb capacity)\n\nGiven the age (16 years) and mileage (153,600), the actual MPG might be slightly lower than these estimates. If fuel economy is your top priority, remember that the 2005 model with the 6.0L V8 would likely get slightly better mileage. However, the 2008's price being $3,232 below market value could offset the fuel cost difference.",
      "sender": "assistant",
      "index": 17,
      "created_at": "2024-10-22T00:13:05.957378Z",
      "updated_at": "2024-10-22T00:13:05.957378Z",
